<br>
For those who do not know, when the government had the airlines regulated, they deemed the airlines should compensate travel agents for their work.<br>
Way back when the compensation was 10 percent uncapped from any base fare.<br>
<br>
Back in 1995, Delta Airlines took a big step and capped the commision an agent could make, all the airlines followed.<br>
Since then Delta has started every cap movement, with the rest of the lemming airlines following in step.<br>
<br>
As of last year, our commision was 5 percent of base, capped at $20.00 per reservation. <br>
We could barely get by on that, but managed, and with a smile on our faces.<br>
<br>
Recently Delta decided nomorecommissionforyou!<br>
99 percent of the airlines followed suit.<br>
<br>
Sooooo basically they want us to work for free, while maintaining an 80 percent booking status that we did before.<br>
<br>
Pardon me Delta while i go sell a cruise!<br>
<br>
Now before you say that this rant doesn't apply to me, it does.<br>
You see, in order to use a travel agent, now you will most likely have to pay a hefty fee to use them.<br>
Well, the traveller says, i will use the internet! <br>
Guess who has fees now too? dingdingding you guessed it! The internet sites! <br>
<br>
Want a paper ticket with the internet? That'll be an extra 12.95 sir!<br>
<br>
So i guess you are going to call the airline directly right? Well be prepared to sit on hold for lord knows how long only to talk to some minimum wage person who could give a flying rats ass about your needs.<br>
<br>
And to the resourcefull person who thinks they will use Orbitz, travelocity, etc to check the fares and then call the airline, be prepared brother, cause before too long they will charge you just to check.<br>
<br>
So, in the Long run, Delta has now passed on all the added expense to you, the consumer.<br>
Fares are high enough as it is with the jet fuel prices, and are a pain in the ass already with the added security measures(make sure you wear clean socks cause your gonna have to take your shoes off!)<br>
<br>
I hope the government sees through the bullshit, remembers that they already saved the airlines from themselves countless times already, and regulates the crap out of them.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you made it this far, thank you for listening. <br>
As a travel agent, i am sorry that this has happened. Partly sorry for my lost revenue. Mostly sorry that regular people have to fit the bill. <p><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/27/27446/pages/59946/crosig1copy.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umaximoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>maximoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#333333>(4/13/02 12:59:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=166.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.planetrivera.com/images/D.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Airlines remove commissions from travel agents</span><hr size=1> This isnt to be funny, but...<br>
